[0.000, "o", "\u001b[0m"]
[0.001, "o", "\u001b[1;34mOther polymorphism: route the BIF either towards String or towards RexxText,\r\n"]
[0.000, "o", "\u001b[0m"]
[0.000, "o", "\u001b[1;34min function of the compatibility of the arguments with String:\r\n"]
[0.000, "o", "\u001b[0m"]
[0.001, "o", "\u001b[1;34mBIF(str1, str2, ..., strN)\r\n"]
[0.000, "o", "\u001b[0m"]
[0.000, "o", "\u001b[1;34m    --> forward to String (byte-oriented) if str's encoding is Byte or UTF-8 (with ASCII characters only)\r\n\u001b[0m"]
[0.000, "o", "\u001b[1;34m    --> forward to RexxText otherwise\r\n\u001b[0m"]
[0.001, "o", "\u001b[1;34m\r\n\u001b[0m"]
[0.000, "o", "\u001b[1;34mAbandonned because we have already the polymorphism on RexxString/RexxText which\r\n"]
[0.000, "o", "\u001b[0m"]
[0.000, "o", "\u001b[1;34mis more easy to control and to understand.\r\n"]
[0.001, "o", "\u001b[0m"]
[0.000, "o", "\u001b[1;34m*/\r\n\u001b[0m"]
